# Architecture Rules

## General

* Organize code by feature/domain.
* Follow SOLID, DRY, KISS, and Separation of Concerns.
* Keep features self-contained.
* Prefer composition over inheritance.

## App

* Only application-level concerns belong here.
* Keep global pages, layouts, providers, and routing in `app/`.
* Do not place business logic in `app/`.

## Shared

* Only place code in `shared/` when used by multiple features.
* Do not put business-specific logic in `shared/`.
* Prefer keeping code inside a feature until reuse is proven.

## Features

* Each feature owns its pages, components, hooks, services, and types.
* Keep business logic inside the feature.
* Avoid direct dependencies between unrelated features.

## Pages

* Route-level components only.
* Keep pages thin.
* Delegate logic to hooks and services.

## Components

* Focus on UI and presentation.
* Single responsibility.
* No direct API calls.
* Reusable only within their feature unless shared.

## Hooks

* Encapsulate reusable business logic and state.
* Manage side effects when appropriate.
* Avoid UI rendering logic.

## Services

* Handle API and external communication.
* No UI logic.
* No state management.

## Types

* Feature-specific types stay in the feature.
* Shared types belong in `shared/types`.

## Store

* Use Zustand only for global client state.
* Do not store server state in Zustand.
* Prefer local state when global state is unnecessary.

## State Management

* React State → Local UI state
* React Hook Form → Form state
* TanStack Query → Server state
* Zustand → Global client state

## Imports

Allowed:

```text
app → feature
app → shared

feature → own feature
feature → shared
```

Avoid:

```text
feature → unrelated feature
shared → feature
```

## Data Flow

```text
Page
→ Hook
→ Service
→ API
```

Never:

```text
Page
→ API
```